# MongoDB Atlas Configuration
# Replace the placeholder values with your actual MongoDB Atlas credentials

# MongoDB URI format for Atlas:
# mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/microfinance_db?appName=Cluster0

# Example with placeholder values:
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://your_username:your_password@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/microfinance_db?appName=Cluster0

# Notes:
# 1. Replace 'your_username' with your MongoDB Atlas database user
# 2. Replace 'your_password' with your MongoDB Atlas database user password (URL-encode special chars: @ becomes %40, etc.)
# 3. Replace 'cluster0.xxxxx' with your actual cluster connection string from MongoDB Atlas
# 4. Ensure your IP address is whitelisted in MongoDB Atlas Network Access settings
# 5. For local development without MongoDB Atlas, use:
#    MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/microfinance_db
